Properties worth millions of Naira belonging to Akoko Anglican Grammar School in Arigidi Akoko, Akoko North-West Local Government Area of Ondo, were destroyed by fire on Sunday The inferno which started around 9 am affected the workshops of the skill acquisition centre of the secondary school, razing the whole department before help could reach the school. According to an eye witness, the technical department of the school was completely destroyed, while items like sewing machines, hairdryers and some other vocational equipment in the school were destroyed. ALSO READ: How my boyfriend sold me as slave to Mali for N350 at 16 years ― Victim Ondo doctors’ strike: No plan to sanction striking… Ondo Navy imposes curfew in Ilaje Two dragged to court over conspiracy, false information in… Resident doctors protest, embark on strike in Ondo over… He said: “So many important equipments were destroyed by the fire which raged for more than an hour. The men of the state fire service were not seeing at the scene to put out the fire. “The Ikare Akoko Fire Station is the nearest to the scene of the incident but we can’t find the fire brigade to do something on the fire, maybe it is because they don’t have functional vehicles.” In his reaction, the Police Public Relations Officer of the state, Mr Femi Joseph, confirmed the incident but said the cause of the inferno was still unknown. ” We have commenced an investigation into the matter,” Joseph said STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE